The operator formula_41 is known as the time-evolution operator, and it is unitary: it preserves the inner product between vectors in the Hilbert space. Unitarity is a general feature of time evolution under the Schrödinger equation. If the initial state is formula_42, then the state at a later time formula_4 will be given by
formula_44
for some unitary operator formula_45. Conversely, suppose that formula_45 is a continuous family of unitary operators parameterized by formula_4. Without loss of generality, the parameterization can be chosen so that formula_48 is the identity operator and that formula_49 for any formula_50. Then formula_45 depends upon the parameter formula_4 in such a way that
